
== Launch Configuration UI
	
		The ï»¿
		`org.eclipse.debug.ui`
		plugin provides a user interface for the launch
		configurations.
	
	A popular example for java developers is the java launch
		configuration dialog.
	
		<mediaobject>
			<imageobject>
				<imagedata fileref="images/sample_java_application_launch_config_ui.png" />
			</imageobject>
		</mediaobject>
	
	
		Previously we created a launch configuration delegate and in order run
		it from the UI, we
		can use the
		`org.eclipse.debug.ui.launchConfigurationTabGroups`
		extension
		point.
	
	
		<programlisting language="xml">
			<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
				parse="text" href="./examples/custom_launch/launchConfigurationTabGroup.adoc[]
		</programlisting>
	
	
		Here we reference to the
		`com.example.launchConfigurationType`
		, which we
		previously created.
	
	
		Before we implement the tab group, we define a custom
		`AbstractLaunchConfigurationTab`
		, which will be placed on the tab
		group.
	
	
		<programlisting language="java">
			<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
				parse="text" href="./examples/custom_ui_launch/SampleTab.java" />
		</programlisting>
	
	
		With this tab we can set our
		`SampleLaunchConfigurationAttributes.CONSOLE_TEXT`
		attribute to the
		`ILaunchConfiguration`
		.
	
	
		In the
		`com.example.SampleTabGroup`
		, we can use existing
		`AbstractLaunchConfigurationTab`
		implementations, like the
		`CommonTab`
		, or the
		`SampleTab`
		from above.
	
	
		<programlisting language="java">
			<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
				parse="text" href="./examples/custom_ui_launch/SampleTabGroup.java" />
		</programlisting>
	
	
		A specific icon for the launch configuration can be defined by using
		the
		`org.eclipse.debug.ui.launchConfigurationTypeImages`
		extension point.
	
		
		<programlisting language="xml">
			<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
				parse="text" href="./examples/custom_ui_launch/launchConfigurationTypeImages.adoc[]
		</programlisting>
	
